description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated and organised individual to be responsible for the environments of particular care settings based at Highbury Hospital The individual will ensure the environments are clean , tidy, safe and comfortable and maintained to appropriate standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to assess the care settings you are responsible for and develop relevant processes to maintain these areas. Experience of auditing will be beneficial.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will need to be able to communicate with the wider professional community and network with relevant departments and agencies to support the role . A good knowledge of IT and previous experience in healthcare settings is essential. You will work as part of a team and need to demonstrate positive team work values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alison Harrison - Service Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: alison.harrison@nottshc.nhs.uk / Telephone number: 0115 9691300 x 16366&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Steve Hill - Modern Matron&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: steve.hill @nottshc.nhs.uk / Telephone number: 01159691300 x 14959&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*The closing date given is a guide. We reserve the right to close the post early once we have received a sufficient number of applicants, so we advise you to submit your application early to prevent disappointment. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*We will be requesting references by email.  Please ensure you include email addresses and contact numbers for your referees to avoid delay in the recruitment process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
